1
00:00:01,890 --> 00:00:04,350
Instructor: Now, let me show you something odd.

2
00:00:04,350 --> 00:00:06,630
Let me switch back to the code here

3
00:00:06,630 --> 00:00:09,663
and let me comment out this Update statement.

4
00:00:10,620 --> 00:00:15,330
With that commented out, let me run the application again

5
00:00:15,330 --> 00:00:19,563
and see what happens this time when we try to update.

6
00:00:21,360 --> 00:00:24,603
So, let me log in again as customer here.

7
00:00:26,340 --> 00:00:28,860
And let me go to Details.

8
00:00:28,860 --> 00:00:30,903
Add this 10 items.

9
00:00:31,740 --> 00:00:35,460
I will go back here. Count is four and three.

10
00:00:35,460 --> 00:00:39,393
When we hit Add To Cart, what do you think would happen?

11
00:00:40,620 --> 00:00:41,550
You would think that

12
00:00:41,550 --> 00:00:44,520
because you commented out that Update statement,

13
00:00:44,520 --> 00:00:46,380
nothing will happen.

14
00:00:46,380 --> 00:00:49,920
But, to your surprise, if we refresh here,

15
00:00:49,920 --> 00:00:53,703
you can see count is updated to 14 from four.

16
00:00:54,720 --> 00:00:56,940
How did that magic happen?

17
00:00:56,940 --> 00:01:00,480
We do not have the Update statement that has been invoked.

18
00:01:00,480 --> 00:01:03,060
So, how can it update that?

19
00:01:03,060 --> 00:01:07,620
Answer to that is power of Entity Framework Core.

20
00:01:07,620 --> 00:01:11,520
What happens here is right here on line 46,

21
00:01:11,520 --> 00:01:14,340
you are retrieving a ShoppingCart.

22
00:01:14,340 --> 00:01:17,760
When you retrieve something with Entity Framework Core,

23
00:01:17,760 --> 00:01:20,760
it is constantly tracking that.

24
00:01:20,760 --> 00:01:23,070
And then on line 56-

25
00:01:23,070 --> 00:01:26,070
well, not here, on line 51,

26
00:01:26,070 --> 00:01:29,520
we have updated count of a shopping cart

27
00:01:29,520 --> 00:01:34,200
or an object that was tracked by Entity Framework Core.

28
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:36,330
So, it is tracking that okay.

29
00:01:36,330 --> 00:01:40,260
You have updated account of the ShoppingCart object

30
00:01:40,260 --> 00:01:43,710
and when we are calling unitOfWork.Save,

31
00:01:43,710 --> 00:01:47,250
it will go ahead and update that change.

32
00:01:47,250 --> 00:01:50,430
So, even though you are not calling Update here,

33
00:01:50,430 --> 00:01:53,640
Entity Framework Core is already tracking that

34
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:56,913
and because of that it will automatically update.

35
00:01:57,930 --> 00:02:01,080
The feature that is provided with Entity Framework Core

36
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:02,790
is a great feature.

37
00:02:02,790 --> 00:02:06,480
But, in some situations, if you are not careful,

38
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:09,393
it can be harmful for your application.

39
00:02:10,410 --> 00:02:12,990
Because of that, what I personally like

40
00:02:12,990 --> 00:02:16,740
is when I am retrieving something using the Get,

41
00:02:16,740 --> 00:02:19,860
it should not track that entity.

42
00:02:19,860 --> 00:02:24,183
We can change that default behavior in the Repository.

43
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:26,430
What we can do is-

44
00:02:26,430 --> 00:02:29,160
let me go to our Repository

45
00:02:29,160 --> 00:02:31,230
and where we have the Get,

46
00:02:31,230 --> 00:02:32,220
right here,

47
00:02:32,220 --> 00:02:36,510
let me add one more property, which will be Boolean flag.

48
00:02:36,510 --> 00:02:38,853
And, by default, it will be false.

49
00:02:40,020 --> 00:02:41,520
Let me save that

50
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:44,790
and we will have to stop the application.

51
00:02:44,790 --> 00:02:48,120
Implement that in the Repository

52
00:02:48,120 --> 00:02:51,750
where we have the Get right here.

53
00:02:51,750 --> 00:02:54,480
I will add that tracked flag here

54
00:02:54,480 --> 00:02:58,740
and then, basically, we will have to add an if condition.

55
00:02:58,740 --> 00:03:00,960
If tracked is true,

56
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:04,950
then whatever we are doing here, that looks good.

57
00:03:04,950 --> 00:03:07,230
But, if tracked is false,

58
00:03:07,230 --> 00:03:10,230
then we will have to modify things.

59
00:03:10,230 --> 00:03:14,460
So, I can copy that, paste it in the else here

60
00:03:14,460 --> 00:03:16,800
and where we have the dbSet,

61
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:19,147
we have to add the AsNoTracking.

62
00:03:20,220 --> 00:03:23,100
That will make sure that Entity Framework Core

63
00:03:23,100 --> 00:03:26,133
does not track the entity that is being retrieved.

64
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:31,170
With that configured, let me run the application.

65
00:03:31,170 --> 00:03:33,960
And now, if you add items to the cart,

66
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:37,113
it will not automatically update the count.

67
00:03:38,220 --> 00:03:40,623
Let me add 12 more here.

68
00:03:42,450 --> 00:03:45,720
We have to log in. I forgot that.

69
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:49,470
And let me try updating six more.

70
00:03:49,470 --> 00:03:52,110
If I go back to SQL server,

71
00:03:52,110 --> 00:03:55,590
this time the count does not get updated

72
00:03:55,590 --> 00:03:57,960
and that is how it should be.

73
00:03:57,960 --> 00:04:00,000
When you have to update anything,

74
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:02,280
you should be explicit about that.

75
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:04,920
Only then it should work.

76
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:09,090
Before I end the video, if I go back to the Repository,

77
00:04:09,090 --> 00:04:10,920
we have a false code here

78
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:13,923
and there is many repetition right here.

79
00:04:14,820 --> 00:04:18,360
We can simplify that by taking the query out,

80
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:21,993
pasting that out of the if-else condition.

81
00:04:23,730 --> 00:04:27,543
And the Iqueryable, we will add that right here.

82
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:32,820
If tracked, then we will say query is dbSet.

83
00:04:32,820 --> 00:04:36,633
Else, we will say query is equal to dbSet.AsNoTracking.

84
00:04:40,410 --> 00:04:41,820
That looks good.

85
00:04:41,820 --> 00:04:44,223
Let me restart the application.

86
00:04:45,930 --> 00:04:47,340
And perfect.

87
00:04:47,340 --> 00:04:49,830
With that, it should be functional.

88
00:04:49,830 --> 00:04:54,360
Now, all we have to do is enable the Update statement here

89
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:57,813
and, with that, it will be able to update ShoppingCart.

90
00:04:59,670 --> 00:05:01,953
Let me log in again here.

91
00:05:03,810 --> 00:05:06,570
And for the Dark Skies,

92
00:05:06,570 --> 00:05:08,283
update by four.

93
00:05:09,390 --> 00:05:11,400
We had 14.

94
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:14,490
And perfect. Now, it's 18.

95
00:05:14,490 --> 00:05:18,210
With that, we have learned an important thing with EF Core,

96
00:05:18,210 --> 00:05:20,193
which is AsNoTracking.

97
00:05:21,060 --> 00:05:22,770
One thing before I go is,

98
00:05:22,770 --> 00:05:26,970
if I go back, and where we have the ShoppingCart,

99
00:05:26,970 --> 00:05:31,320
we can add some TempData to display notification.

100
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:36,320
So, right here I will say, "Cart updated successfully."

101
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:37,980
Let me restart

102
00:05:37,980 --> 00:05:41,523
and make sure we see the toaster notification.

103
00:05:49,740 --> 00:05:51,753
And perfect. That works.

104
00:05:52,740 --> 00:05:56,943
With that in place, let me continue from the next video.

